chart_description: This chart shows the request latency in seconds for the AWS cluster autoscaler broken down by verb and URL. It is useful for identifying potential performance bottlenecks and optimizing the response time of the autoscaler.

dimension_descriptions.bucket_+Inf: The number of requests that took more than 0.512 seconds to complete.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.004: The number of requests that took between 0 and 0.004 seconds to complete.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.008: The number of requests that took between 0.004 and 0.008 seconds to complete.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.016: The number of requests that took between 0.008 and 0.016 seconds to complete.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.032: The number of requests that took between 0.016 and 0.032 seconds to complete.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.064: The number of requests that took between 0.032 and 0.064 seconds to complete.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.128: The number of requests that took between 0.064 and 0.128 seconds to complete.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.256: The number of requests that took between 0.128 and 0.256 seconds to complete.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.512: The number of requests that took between 0.256 and 0.512 seconds to complete.
